 10  # Sesquilinear form
 11  
 12  This file defines a bilinear form over a module. The definition requires a ring antiautomorphism
 13  on the scalar ring, which comes from the file ring_theory.involution. Basic ideas such as
 14  orthogonality are also introduced.
 15  
 16  A sesquilinear form on an R-module M, is a function from M x M to R, that is linear in the first argument
 17  and antilinear in the second, with respect to an antiautomorphism on R (an antiisomorphism from R to R).
 18  
 19  ## Notations
 20  
 21  Given any term S of type sesq_form, due to a coercion, can use the notation S x y to
 22  refer to the function field, ie. S x y = S.bilin x y.
 23  
 24  ## References
 25  
 26  * <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sesquilinear_form#Over_arbitrary_rings>
 27
